	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Revnd Mr Leeser</addressee>&#8212;<date>March 24th&#45;49</date></p>
				<p><persName role="author">Mrs Eckard</persName> <placeName>No 68 So 8th St.</placeName><lb/> takes the liberty of requesting<lb/> tickets of admission&#44; if tickets are<lb/> required&#44; to the Consecration&#44; of the<lb/> new Synagogue in <placeName>Crown St.</placeName>  <persName role="author">Mrs<lb/> Eckard</persName> has several friends strangers<lb/> in the City&#44; who no doubt would<lb/> be happy to witness the solemn<lb/> and interesting scene.  We all<lb/> love your people my dear Sir.  The<lb/> time is not far distant when we&#44; as<lb/> dear <persName>Miss Aguillar</persName> now does&#44; shall<lb/> see<lb/> &#34;Eye to Eye.&#34;  May I beg you sir&#44; in<lb/> case you <sic>authorise</sic> our admission<lb/> to say at what hour we had best<lb/> be there.  With Great respect</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Susan R E</persName>&#95;&#95;&#95;</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p><addressee>Revnd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Walnut St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>P. a.</placeName></p>
